history.content: The EE Scheduler only works part time. If you completed the form four days ago (2 of which were a weekend), she likely hasn't reviewed your request yet. Given that CS Education Day is bringing 600 extra people to the department tomorrow, It won't be looked at before Wednesday.

children.subject:
The email was from Cal Central, unrelated the the google form our department processes. All waitlisted students receive an email saying they haven't been unenrollled. 


It sounds like you have a lot of questions about the enrollment system. Please contact sishelp@berkeley.edu

I only received that "Time Conflict" email once before I filled out the form, along with a saying that I would only receive that once. However, now I received the same email everyday. What should I do to "unsubscribe" this email?

I am not sure about the "drop and reenroll" mechanism. How does it work? And, should I do that?

history.content:
I am a CS major junior. I am on the waitlist of EE16B, which has time conflict with another class that I have enrolled. I filled out EE Conflict Override Form about four days ago, and since then, I received an email everyday saying that "You have NOT been enrolled from the wait list into EE16B". 

The email mentioned: "Actions you can take: Drop the time-conflicted class and reenroll into the dropped class to trigger receipt of time conflict override notification." I feel hesitated following this suggestion. Why does "drop and reenroll" override time conflict? I am afraid that one I dropped the class, I will be put on the end of waitlist, and be even harder to get in.

Who should I go to and what action can I take now?
history.subject: EE 16B Enrollment Issue
